This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) because it proposes an unsupervised keyphrase extraction model that encodes topical information within a multipartite graph structure. The paper also mentions experiments conducted on three widely used datasets, which is a common practice in the NLP community. 

The paper may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category because keyphrase extraction is a common task in IR and the proposed model aims to improve candidate ranking. 

The Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category is also a possibility because the model exploits the mutually reinforcing relationship between keyphrase candidates and topics to improve ranking, which is a common approach in machine learning. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is another possibility because the proposed model uses a novel mechanism to incorporate keyphrase selection preferences, which is a common problem in AI. 

Finally, the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category is a less likely possibility because the proposed model uses a graph structure to represent keyphrase candidates and topics, which is a common topic in DS research.
